अंशु
Aṃśu. — I. Name of a protégé of the Aśvins in the Rigveda.^1<BR>2. Dhānaṃjayya, pupil of Amāvāsya Śāṇḍilyāyana, according<BR>to the Vaṃśa Brāhmaṇa.^2<BR>1) viii. 5, 26. Cf. Ludwig, Transla-<BR>tion of the Rigveda, 3, 160; Hopkins,<BR>Journal of the American Oriental Society,<BR>17, 89; Sieg, Die Sagenstoffe des Ṛgveda,<BR>129, suggests that he may be identical<BR>with Khela.<BR>2) Indische Studien, 4, 373.<BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?cp=1-001&d=VEI" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?d=vei&e=1" target="_blank">Correction</a>

