Krumu is the name of a stream mentioned twice in the<BR>Rigveda — once in the fifth book^1 and once in the last, in the<BR>Nadī-stuti, or ‘praise of rivers.’^2 There can be little doubt<BR>that this river is identical with the modern Kurum, a western<BR>tributary of the Indus.^3<BR>1) v. 53, 9.<BR>2) x. 75, 6.<BR>3) Roth, Nirukta, Erläuterungen, 43;<BR>Zimmer, Altindisches Leben, 14: Lud-<BR>wig, Translation of the Rigveda, 3,<BR>200.<BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?cp=1-199&d=VEI" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?d=vei&e=780" target="_blank">Correction</a>

