क्रोश
Krośa, as a measure of distance (lit. ‘a shout,’ as expressing<BR>the range of the voice), is found in the Pañcaviṃśa Brāhmaṇa.^1<BR>1) xvi. 13, 12. Cf. Weber, Indische<BR>Studien, 8, 432 et seq. In the later<BR>literature it is equivalent to about two<BR>miles. The word still survives in the<BR>vernacular form of Kos as the most<BR>popular measure of distance in India.<BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?cp=1-199&d=VEI" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?d=vei&e=783" target="_blank">Correction</a>

