तूपर
Tūpara, ‘hornless,’ is a frequent description of animals<BR>intended for the sacrifice, especially of the goat, in the<BR>Atharvaveda and later.^1<BR>1) Av. xi. 9, 22; Taittirīya Saṃhitā,<BR>ii. 1, 1, 4, etc.; Vājasaneyi Saṃhitā,<BR>xxiv. 1, 15; xxix. 59, etc.; Satapatha<BR>Brāhmaṇa, v. 1, 3, 7, etc.<BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?cp=1-318&d=VEI" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?d=vei&e=1177" target="_blank">Correction</a>

