भजेरथ
Bhaje-ratha is mentioned in one passage of the Rigveda,^1<BR>where Ludwig^2 thinks a place-name is meant. Griffith^3 is<BR>doubtful whether the word is the name of a place or a man.<BR>Roth^4 was inclined to see a corruption of the text.^5 Cf.<BR>Bhagīratha.<BR>1) x. 60, 2.<BR>2) Translation of the Rigveda, 3, 138,<BR>165.<BR>3) Hymns of the Rigveda, 2, 463.<BR>4) St. Petersburg Dictionary, s.v.<BR>5) Grassmann, Wörterbuch, s.v., thinks<BR>that the compound should be read as<BR>two words: bhaje rathasya (satpatim),<BR>‘to win (the lord) of the car.’<BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?cp=2-094&d=VEI" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?d=vei&e=2233" target="_blank">Correction</a>

