भाल्लविन्
Bhāllavin, ‘pupil of Bhallavin,’ is the name of a school of<BR>teachers mentioned in the Jaiminīya Upaniṣad Brāhmaṇa.^1<BR>1) ii. 4, 7 (spelt Bhāllabin). Cf.<BR>Weber, Indische Studien, 1, 44; 2, 100;<BR>390; Nidāna Sūtra, v. 1; Anupada<BR>Sūtra, ii. 1; vii. 12; Bṛhaddevatā<BR>v. 23. 159.<BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?cp=2-102&d=VEI" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?d=vei&e=2264" target="_blank">Correction</a>

