सुकरीर
Su-karīra in the Maitrāyaṇī Saṃhitā (ii. 7, 5) is a misreading<BR>of su-kurīra. See Kurīra.<BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?cp=2-452&d=VEI" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?d=vei&e=3585" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सुकीर्तिकाक्षीवत
Su-kīrti Kākṣīvata (‘descendant of Kakṣīvant’) is the name<BR>of a Ṛṣi to whom the Brāhmaṇas of the Rigveda^1 ascribe the<BR>authorship of a Vedic hymn.^2<BR>1) Aitareya Brāhmaṇa, v. 15, 4; vi. 29, 1; Kauṣītaki Brāhmaṇa, xxx. 5.<BR>2) x. 131.<BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?cp=2-452&d=VEI" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?d=vei&e=3586" target="_blank">Correction</a>

