Su-kha. See Kha.<BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?cp=2-453&d=VEI" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?d=vei&e=3589" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सुगन्धितेजन
Sugandhi-tejana in the later Saṃhitās^1 and the Brāhmaṇas^2<BR>denotes a kind of fragrant grass.<BR>1) Taittirīya Saṃhitā, vi. 2, 8, 4;<BR>Kāṭhaka Saṃhitā, xxv. 6.<BR>2) Aitareya Brāhmaṇa, i. 28, 28;<BR>Satapatha Brāhmaṇa, iii. 5, 2, 17;<BR>Pañcaviṃśa Brāhmaṇa, xxiv. 13, 5.<BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?cp=2-453&d=VEI" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?d=vei&e=3590" target="_blank">Correction</a>

